content.description: For the first time in franchise history, the Chicago Sky are WNBA Champions. In Game 4 on Sunday, the Sky trailed for the majority of the game, but were able to pull off a 14 point comeback. Kahleah Copper was named Finals MVP after averaging 17 points and 5.5 rebounds in the series.
content.name: Game 4 Mini Movie: The Chicago Sky Become the 2021 WNBA Champions
